ConvertFrom-StringData @'
###PSLOC
OSVersion = Operating System version is '{0}'. Expected '{1}'
OSBuild = Operating System on '{0}' build is '{1}'. Expected '{2}'
OSVersionSkip = Cannot determine desired operation system version.
MinOSCheck = Operating System version on '{0}' is '{1}' and should be greater than or equal to '{2}'
OSVersionRemediation = All cluster nodes must run the same OS version as the orchestrator. Update the OS on any nodes reporting a version mismatch.
NTPServerCheck = NTP server is configured on '{0}' as '{1}'. Expected '{2}'
NTPServerNotSet = NTP server is not configured on '{0}'. Currently set to '{1}'
NtpStripChartPass = NTP Response received on '{0}' from '{1}', current time and local offset: '{2}'.
NtpStripChartFail = NTP Response not received on '{0}' from '{1}': '{2}'.
NTPServerCheckPass = NTP servers are configured consistently across all nodes. {0}
NTPServerCheckFail = NTP servers are not configured consistently across all nodes. {0} Please configure NTP servers consistently across all nodes.
NTPServerRemediation = Configure an external NTP time source on all nodes using 'w32tm /config /manualpeerlist:<ntp-server> /syncfromflags:manual /reliable:yes /update'. Ensure all nodes point to the same NTP server.
NTPConsistencyRemediation = All cluster nodes must use the same NTP server. Run 'w32tm /query /source' on each node and correct any mismatches.
NTPSyncRemediation = Ensure all nodes can reach the configured NTP server. Verify firewall rules allow outbound UDP port 123 and run 'w32tm /resync /force' to re-synchronize.
LocalGroupEnumerationFailure = Unable to enumerate local groups on '{0}' using Get-LocalGroupMember -SID S-1-5-32-544. Error: '{1}'
LocalGroupEnumerationSuccess = Local group enumeration on '{0}' succeeded.
LocalGroupRemediation = The local Administrators group contains stale or orphaned SID references. Remove invalid members from the Administrators group using 'net localgroup Administrators' and 'Remove-LocalGroupMember'.
IsNotPartofDomainSuccess = '{0}' is not part of a domain.
IsNotPartofDomainFailure = '{0}' is part of a domain. Please remove '{0}' from the domain.
DomainMembershipRemediation = Nodes must not be domain-joined before deployment. Remove the node from the domain using 'Remove-Computer -UnjoinDomainCredential <cred> -Force' and restart.
